I resumed play a couple of days ago and WOW the games have been
totally interesting and wild!!!!


On 26-Nov-01, Stefan wrote:

SP> - The LOS of a creature sometimes changes after pressing "l" a
SP>   few times

Of course, because the animated creature that was blocking the LOS
has just moved his arm or leg out of the way.  Chaos uses real-time
raytracing to determine LOS.

If you point at anything on the board with the mouse and then hold down
the "l" key you can watch the LOS changing in real-time.  Its really
cool.


SP> - Is there any spell that can be spoken on an enemy
SP>   invulnerable wizard?

Yes, all of them.

SP>  Will such a wizard die of a growth like Green Ooze?

Yes.

Irvine's Invulnerability only protects you from standard combat
attacks.  This includes combat, ranged combat and special combat.
It does not protect against being covered over by tons of Green
Oozy crap. :)


SP> - Why do you get a spell for speaking justice on a wizard with
SP>   less than 4 magic resistance, although he doesn't die?

Because you "virtually" killed him.


SP> - Why do I get no spell for killing an hole, although it has
SP>   63 energy?

Do you think you deserve a bonus spell for killing a defenseless
hole in the ground?!?  :)


SP> - do the different meditation places provide a different number
SP>   of spells to choose from?

I think they are all the same except the Shadow City gives more.  The
Shadow City rules!


JB> Is it possible to swap the creature that stands on top of the scroll
JB> with another one of your creatures in a movephase
JB> without losing 'scroll delay' turn count on it?

Yes, absolutely.  You are allowed to shuffle your creatures during
your turn with no penalty.


